    "summary": "Maria Chalevelaki holds a PhD in Linguistics with a specialisation in Semiotics. Her doctoral dissertation explored fashion industry branding using the tools of semiotics from Universit\u00e9 Lyon II. For several years she taught semiology and visual culture in the Department of Communication at Lyon II Lumi\u00e8re University and in the Department of Graphic Design of the Technological Educational Institute of Athens. During 2010-2011 she held a grant for post-doctoral research on Visual Culture at the School of Communication, Media and Culture of Panteion University,where she lectured at the undergraduate and graduate level. She has also supervised MA theses for the Hellenic Open University.\nShe is the author of a commercially successful book on applied semiotics. Her book is taught at twelve departments of higher education (i.e. Department of Architecture, Sociology, Graphic Design, Fashion). She has presented papers at international conferences and has published in scientific journals. Her scientific interests revolve around semiotics, linguistics, fashion, visual culture and communication. \nShe now lives in Amsterdam and is teaching fashion management courses at the Graduate and Undergraduate level at UIBS. ",
